    "During the 1970s, the development of expert systems aimed to emulate the decision-making processes of human experts through rule-based logic.",
    "Notably, MYCIN (Shortliffe, 1976), developed at Stanford University, served as a prominent example of this technology, focusing on diagnosing bacterial infections and providing treatment recommendations.",
    "The emergence of expert systems like MYCIN showcased the practical implementation of artificial intelligence in specialized domains, particularly where expert knowledge was essential.",
    "In subsequent years, AI has been utilized in customer support to integrate knowledge from various domains, including industry-specific information and product details, to deliver accurate and comprehensive responses to customer inquiries.",
    "The 1980s witnessed the emergence of machine learning, involving the creation of algorithms that allowed computers to learn from data without explicit programming."
